{"descriptions":[{"id":1210,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe copulas \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདུག་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e, etc. are not used in future constructions. Instead, the future forms of the full verbs \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆགས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;to become,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;to do,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོང་ \u003c/span\u003e\u0026ldquo;to come,\u0026rdquo;\u003ca name=\"n1\" href=\"#fn1\"\u003e[1]\u003c/a\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསྡད་ \u003c/span\u003e\u0026ldquo;to stay\u0026rdquo; are used. A distinction may be made between essential and existential statements.\u003c/p\u003e \u003chr size=\"1\" /\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u003ca name=\"fn1\" href=\"#n1\"\u003e[1]\u003c/a\u003e Note that \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོང་\u003c/span\u003e may also mean \u0026ldquo;to be appropriate.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:26 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:26 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}